# Documentation Rules

## General Rules
- Write all documentation in English
- Use clear and concise language
- Keep documentation up to date
- Follow Markdown best practices

## File Structure
- Place all docs in `docs/` directory
- Use kebab-case for filenames
- Include README.md in each directory
- Keep files organized by category

## Content Requirements
- Include title and description
- List prerequisites
- Provide installation steps
- Document configuration
- Add usage examples
- Include troubleshooting
- Add changelog

## Formatting
- Use proper Markdown syntax
- Include code blocks with language
- Use tables for structured data
- Add images when helpful
- Keep line length reasonable

## Examples
```markdown
# Blueprint Title

## Description
Brief description of the blueprint's purpose.

## Prerequisites
- Home Assistant 2025.5.3 or later
- Required integrations
- Required entities

## Installation
1. Copy the blueprint URL
2. Go to Blueprints
3. Click Import Blueprint
4. Paste the URL

## Configuration
| Parameter | Description | Default |
|-----------|-------------|---------|
| entity    | Entity to monitor | - |
| time      | Time to trigger | - |

## Usage
Example configuration and usage scenarios.

## Troubleshooting
Common issues and their solutions.
```

## Best Practices
- Keep documentation simple
- Use consistent formatting
- Include practical examples
- Update when code changes
- Add helpful comments
- Link related documents
- Include version info 